    "The equation of motion for each helicity mode is thenη 2 ∂ 2 ∂η 2 -2η ∂ ∂η + c 2 h,S k 2 η 2 + m 2 H 2 - 2hκ H kη σ h (η, k) = 0.",
    "(2.13)The solution to this equation with Bunch-Davies initial conditions i.e.",
    "the solution that has Minkowski-like behaviour in the far past and satisfies the de Sitter Wronskian condition isσ h (η, k) = e -πκ/2 -Hη 2c h,S k W iκ,ν (2ic h,S kη), ν = 9 4 - m 2 H 2, κ = hκ c h,S H, (2.14) JHEP05(2024)196where W a,b (z) is the Whittaker W -function.",
    "This solution is valid for both light (Im ν = 0) and heavy (Re ν = 0) fields.",
    "In the limit that the chemical potential vanishes we would expect to recover the solution of [88] corresponding to the solution of a massive scalar field in de Sitter space."
